data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** because the new overload takes `Func<>` instead of `Expression<Func<>>`. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Lambda` needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

Two sub-changes:

- **Same-name properties** across complex types now get a numeric suffix (e.g. `Street` → `Street1`) instead of silently sharing a column.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`.

If you have an existing database, **add a migration and inspect it**. To preserve old column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old shorter name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
